#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:1
msgid "Fetching Rules"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:3
msgid ""
"All rule retrieval goes through the `/rules/{rule_id_path}` endpoint. This "
"page covers the full range of retrieval patterns."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:7
msgid "Fetching a complete rule set"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:9
msgid ""
"Omit the rule path after the rule set identifier to retrieve the full set as "
"a single response. The rule set node itself is returned with all its top-"
"level rules."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:11
msgid "GET /rules/BWBR0015703_2025-07-01_0"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:15
msgid ""
"!!! note Large rule sets can produce substantial responses. For most "
"integration work you will want to target a specific rule or article rather "
"than the full set."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:20
msgid "Fetching a specific article"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:22
msgid "Add the article identifier after the rule set ID, separated by a comma:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:24
msgid "GET /rules/BWBR0015703_2025-07-01_0%2C%20Artikel%2020"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:28
msgid "URL-encoding reference: `,` → `%2C`, space → `%20`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:30
msgid ""
"The response includes the article and all its contained sub-rules "
"recursively."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:34
msgid "Navigating to a nested rule"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:36
msgid "Extend the path with additional comma-separated identifiers:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:38
msgid ""
"GET /rules/BWBR0015703_2025-07-"
"01_0%2C%20Artikel%2020%2C%20lid%201%2C%20onderdeel%20a."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:42
msgid ""
"The path traversal is depth-first. Non-alphanumeric characters (spaces, "
"periods, parentheses) are stripped from both the path identifier and the "
"graph identifier before matching, so `\"onderdeel a.\"` and `\"onderdeel "
"a\"` match the same rule node."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:46
msgid "Skipping intermediate identifiers"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:48
msgid ""
"Intermediate levels can be omitted if there is no ambiguity. Both of the "
"following reach the same rule:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:50
msgid ""
"/rules/BWBR0015703_2025-07-01_0%2C%20Artikel%2020%2C%20onderdeel%20a.\n"
"/rules/BWBR0015703_2025-07-"
"01_0%2C%20Artikel%2020%2C%20lid%201%2C%20onderdeel%20a."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:57
msgid "CVDR (municipal regulations)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:59
msgid "Same pattern, with CVDR identifiers:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:61
msgid ""
"GET /rules/CVDR712517_1%2C%20Artikel%205\n"
"GET /rules/CVDR712517                        ← current version\n"
"GET /rules/CVDR712517_2025-07-02_latest      ← valid on date"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:69
msgid "EU CELLAR (European legislation)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:71
msgid ""
"GET /rules/CFMX483e4752e-f2e5-11e8-9982-"
"01aa75ed71a1.0017.02_DOC_2%2C%20Artikel%201"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:77
msgid "Choosing an output format"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:79
msgid ""
"Append `?format=turtle` (or any supported format value) to change "
"serialisation:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:81
msgid ""
"GET /rules/BWBR0015703_2025-07-01_0%2C%20Artikel%2020?format=turtle\n"
"GET /rules/BWBR0015703_2025-07-01_0%2C%20Artikel%2020?format=json-ld"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:86
msgid "See [Output Formats]{1} for the full list."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:90
msgid "Using a custom path delimiter"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:92
msgid ""
"If a rule identifier contains a comma, override the delimiter with "
"`path_delimiter`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:94
msgid "GET /rules/BWBR0015703_2025-07-01_0|Artikel%2020?path_delimiter=%7C"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:100
msgid "Extracting structured values with unformat"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:102
msgid ""
"When a rule definition contains a parseable pattern, `unformat` extracts "
"named fields directly:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:104
msgid ""
"GET /rules/BWBR0015703_2025-07-"
"01_0%2C%20Artikel%2020%2C%20lid%201%2C%20onderdeel%20a.\n"
"    "
"?unformat=%7Bsituatie%3Aparam_value%7D%3A%20%E2%82%AC%20%7Bnorm%3Aparam_value%7D"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:109
msgid ""
"Decoded `unformat` pattern: `{situatie:param_value}: € {norm:param_value}`"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:111
msgid ""
"The response merges the extracted `situatie` and `norm` fields into the "
"cprmv-json output alongside the full rule data."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/cprmv-api%5Cuser-guide%5Cfetching-rules.md:113
msgid "See [Definition Extraction]{1} for more examples."
msgstr ""
